er\nglitching pulsars, which appears genuine and not a result of observational\nbiases. In addition to typical glitches, the smooth spin-down of the pulsar is\nalso affected by an almost continuous activity that can be partially\ncharacterised by small step-like changes in $\\nu$, $\\dot{\\nu,}$ or both.\nSimulations indicate that a continuous wandering of the rotational phase,\nfollowing a red spectrum, could mimic such step-like changes in the timing\nresiduals.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 6 Jul 2020 17:53:11 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 1 Mar 2021 19:26:35 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 12 Apr 2021 17:03:26 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-05-05"}
